{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":634,"text":"I consider it my life's mission"},{"time":3877,"text":"to convey the urgency\nof climate change through my work."},{"time":7961,"text":"I've traveled north to the Arctic\nto the capture the unfolding story"},{"time":11726,"text":"of polar melt,"},{"time":13229,"text":"and south to the Equator to document\nthe subsequent rising seas."},{"time":17903,"text":"Most recently, I visited\nthe icy coast of Greenland"},{"time":21617,"text":"and the low-lying islands of the Maldives,"},{"time":24507,"text":"connecting two seemingly disparate\nbut equally endangered"},{"time":29008,"text":"parts of our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31504,"text":"My drawings explore moments\nof transition, turbulence"},{"time":37571,"text":"and tranquility in the landscape,"},{"time":40309,"text":"allowing viewers to emotionally connect"},{"time":43815,"text":"with a place you might never\nhave the chance to visit."},{"time":47185,"text":"I choose to convey the beauty\nas opposed to the devastation."},{"time":52230,"text":"If you can experience the sublimity\nof these landscapes,"},{"time":56686,"text":"perhaps you'll be inspired\nto protect and preserve them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61545,"text":"Behavioral psychology tells us\nthat we take action"},{"time":64936,"text":"and make decisions based\non our emotions above all else."},{"time":69497,"text":"And studies have shown\nthat art impacts our emotions"},{"time":72957,"text":"more effectively than a scary news report."},{"time":77193,"text":"Experts predict ice-free Arctic summers"},{"time":80661,"text":"as early as 2020."},{"time":83521,"text":"And sea levels are likely to rise\nbetween two and ten feet"},{"time":87712,"text":"by century's end."},{"time":90364,"text":"I have dedicated my career\nto illuminating these projections"},{"time":95064,"text":"with an accessible medium,"},{"time":97152,"text":"one that moves us in a way\nthat statistics may not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102684,"text":"My process begins\nwith traveling to the places"},{"time":105387,"text":"at the forefront of climate change."},{"time":107710,"text":"On-site, I take thousands of photographs."},{"time":110696,"text":"Back in the studio,"},{"time":111963,"text":"I work from both my memory\nof the experience and the photographs"},{"time":116247,"text":"to create very large-scale compositions,"},{"time":118526,"text":"sometimes over 10 feet wide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121412,"text":"I draw with soft pastel, which is dry\nlike charcoal, but colors."},{"time":126456,"text":"I consider my work drawings\nbut others call them painting."},{"time":130203,"text":"I cringe, though, when I'm referred to\nas a \"finger painter.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":134248,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135390,"text":"But I don't use any tools"},{"time":137719,"text":"and I have always used\nmy fingers and palms"},{"time":140220,"text":"to manipulate the pigment on the paper."},{"time":143990,"text":"Drawing is a form of meditation for me."},{"time":148354,"text":"It quiets my mind."},{"time":150437,"text":"I don't perceive what I'm drawing"},{"time":152268,"text":"as ice or water."},{"time":153665,"text":"Instead, the image is stripped down"},{"time":156151,"text":"to its most basic form of color and shape."},{"time":160964,"text":"Once the piece is complete,"},{"time":162330,"text":"I can finally experience\nthe composition as a whole,"},{"time":165490,"text":"as an iceberg floating\nthrough glassy water,"},{"time":168076,"text":"or a wave cresting with foam."},{"time":171884,"text":"On average, a piece this size\ntakes me about,"},{"time":175830,"text":"as you can see, 10 seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177544,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179348,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183336,"text":"Really, more like 200 hours,\n250 hours for something that size."},{"time":187816,"text":"But I've been drawing ever since\nI could hold a crayon, really."},{"time":190822,"text":"My mom was an artist, and growing up,"},{"time":192759,"text":"we always had art supplies\nall over the house."},{"time":195269,"text":"My mother's love of photography"},{"time":197846,"text":"propelled her to the most\nremote regions of the earth,"},{"time":201405,"text":"and my family and I were fortunate enough"},{"time":203835,"text":"to join and support her\non these adventures."},{"time":207139,"text":"We rode camels in Northern Africa"},{"time":209871,"text":"and mushed on dog sleds\nnear the North Pole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213871,"text":"In August of 2012,\nI led my first expedition,"},{"time":218091,"text":"taking a group of artists and scholars\nup the northwest coast of Greenland."},{"time":224232,"text":"My mother was originally\nsupposed to lead this trip."},{"time":227146,"text":"She and I were in the early\nstages of planning,"},{"time":229885,"text":"as we had intended to go together,"},{"time":232471,"text":"when she fell victim to a brain tumor."},{"time":235812,"text":"The cancer quickly took over\nher body and mind,"},{"time":239833,"text":"and she passed away six months later."},{"time":243110,"text":"During the months of her illness, though,"},{"time":245119,"text":"her dedication to the expedition\nnever wavered, and I made a promise"},{"time":250643,"text":"to carry out her final journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253374,"text":"My mother's passion for the Arctic"},{"time":256541,"text":"echoed through my experience in Greenland,"},{"time":259938,"text":"and I felt the power"},{"time":262938,"text":"and the fragility of the landscape."},{"time":266738,"text":"The sheer size of the icebergs"},{"time":269422,"text":"is humbling."},{"time":271168,"text":"The ice fields are alive\nwith movement and sound"},{"time":274615,"text":"in a way that I never expected."},{"time":277284,"text":"I expanded the scale of my compositions"},{"time":279556,"text":"to give you that same sense of awe\nthat I experienced."},{"time":285021,"text":"Yet, while the grandeur\nof the ice is evident,"},{"time":288740,"text":"so, too, is its vulnerability."},{"time":291042,"text":"From our boat,"},{"time":292281,"text":"I could see the ice sweating\nunder the unseasonably warm sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298940,"text":"We had a chance to visit\nmany of the Inuit communities in Greenland"},{"time":302527,"text":"that now face huge challenges."},{"time":305381,"text":"The locals spoke to me\nof vast areas of sea ice"},{"time":308721,"text":"that are no longer\nfreezing over as they once did."},{"time":311431,"text":"And without ice, their hunting\nand harvesting grounds"},{"time":314533,"text":"are severely diminished,"},{"time":316319,"text":"threatening their way\nof life and survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320616,"text":"The melting glaciers in Greenland"},{"time":322535,"text":"are one of the largest\ncontributing factors to rising sea levels,"},{"time":326903,"text":"which have already begun to drown"},{"time":329043,"text":"some of our world's lowest-lying islands."},{"time":332942,"text":"One year after my trip to Greenland,\nI visited the Maldives,"},{"time":337145,"text":"the lowest and flattest country\nin the entire world."},{"time":340752,"text":"While I was there, I collected\nimages and inspiration"},{"time":344809,"text":"for a new body of work:"},{"time":347072,"text":"drawings of waves lapping\non the coast of a nation"},{"time":351129,"text":"that could be entirely underwater\nwithin this century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357484,"text":"Devastating events happen every day"},{"time":361051,"text":"on scales both global and personal."},{"time":364844,"text":"When I was in Greenland,"},{"time":366131,"text":"I scattered my mother's ashes\namidst the melting ice."},{"time":370743,"text":"Now she remains a part\nof the landscape she loved so much,"},{"time":375854,"text":"even as it, too, passes\nand takes on new form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381095,"text":"Among the many gifts my mother gave me"},{"time":383887,"text":"was the ability to focus on the positive,"},{"time":386911,"text":"rather than the negative."},{"time":389083,"text":"My drawings celebrate the beauty\nof what we all stand to lose."},{"time":395845,"text":"I hope they can serve as records\nof sublime landscapes in flux,"},{"time":401663,"text":"documenting the transition\nand inspiring our global community"},{"time":406309,"text":"to take action for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409102,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410333,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}